40|$|Necessary and {{sufficient}} conditions {{for an alternative}} to be a sophisticated voting outcome under an <b>amendment</b> <b>procedure</b> are derived. The uncovered set, as first defined by Miller (1980), is shown to be potentially reducible, and conditions are determined for which this reduction equals the set of sophisticated voting outcomes. In addition, simple methods are given for calculating both the uncovered set and its reduction...|$|R
